This paper is about language modeling, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also discusses machine learning techniques such as Noise Contrastive Estimation (NCE) and softmax-based approaches, which are commonly used in areas such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper analyzes the errors and regularities in self-normalization algorithms, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of statistical learning (cs.SD).
